 Zipping up the contractions over all 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 sites, in this order, gives a total number of 
\begin_inset Formula $2LpD^{3}$
\end_inset

 operations, instead of 
\begin_inset Formula $p^{L}D^{L}$
\end_inset

, which is a huge gain.
\end_layout

